Preamble

This file checks that the st_difference() actually correctly removed overlapping areas in 02_clean.R. It also establishes that there are some overlaps, which when removed leave little wiggly bits left over.

These could be

  1. ignored
  2. fixed by using something like st_snap before st_difference
  3. removed manually

Load packages

library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(patchwork)

Load protected areas

pa1 <- read_rds("data/CPCAD_Dec2019_BC_clean.rds")
pa2 <- read_rds("data/CPCAD_Dec2019_BC_clean_no_ovlps.rds") %>%
  mutate(area2 = as.numeric(st_area(Shape)))

pa1 = original clean, pa2 with overlaps removed

pa2_df <- st_set_geometry(pa2, NULL) %>%
  group_by(zone_id, name_e) %>%
  summarize(area1 = unique(area1), area2 = sum(area2))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'zone_id'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

Look for features where a lot of overlap was removed

filter(pa2_df, abs(area1 - area2) > 5000000)

Myra - Bellevue Park

bbx <- filter(pa2, str_detect(name_e, "Myra")) %>%
  st_buffer(dist = 1000) %>%
  st_bbox()

sub_pa1 <- st_crop(pa1, bbx)
## Warning: attribute variables are assumed to be spatially constant throughout all geometries
sub_pa2 <- sub_pa1 %>%
  select(zone_id, name_e, oecm, iucn_cat, protdate) %>%
  arrange(oecm, iucn_cat, protdate) %>%
  st_difference()

sub_pa2
## Simple feature collection with 2 features and 5 fields
## geometry type:  MULTIPOLYGON
## dimension:      XY
## bbox:           xmin: -1656061 ymin: 1350467 xmax: -1645356 ymax: 1366948
## projected CRS:  Canada_Albers_Equal_Area_Conic
##     zone_id                       name_e oecm iucn_cat protdate                          Shape
## 1 591000446         Myra - Bellevue Park   No       II     2001 MULTIPOLYGON (((-1651358 13...
## 2 591005024 Myra-Bellevue Protected Area   No      N/A     2007 MULTIPOLYGON (((-1654332 13...
g1 <- ggplot(data = sub_pa1, aes(fill = name_e)) +
  geom_sf(alpha = 0.5) + labs(title = "Orig")
g2 <- ggplot(data = sub_pa2, aes(fill = name_e)) +
  geom_sf(alpha = 0.5) + labs(title = "Overlaps removed")
g1 + g2 + plot_layout(guides = "collect")

(g1 + facet_wrap(~name_e)) / (g2 + facet_wrap(~name_e)) +
  plot_layout(guides = "collect")

Good, no problems, Myra-Vellevue Protected Area includes river, but Myra - Bellevue Park is the rest
